Fix HUD never rendering + nav not opening: script/ScreenGui name collision

The HUD LocalScript is itself named "HUD" (rojo names instances after files), so the
duplicate-guard's FindFirstChild("HUD") matched the SCRIPT and returned before
building any UI — the HUD has been invisible ever since the guard was added.

Same root cause broke the nav: each panel's LocalScript shares its name with the
ScreenGui it creates, so FindFirstChild(name) could return the script, and toggling
.Enabled on it did nothing.

Both now match a real ScreenGui specifically (iterate children, check :IsA("ScreenGui")).
HUD renders again and the bottom-nav buttons open their panels.

